body_html: CI is complaining about one of the preallocated types, i.e. float, which is actually already marked with AT_CORE_EXPORT. This is the correct macro, right? Another possible explanation is that the CAFFE2_UNIQUE_LONG_TYPEMETA macro is screwing something up (i.e. missing when the .cpp file is compiled). @Yangqing do you have an idea?
